me us  billion  total assets  billion   number of employees   website wwwglencorecom glencore plc an acronym for global energy commodity resources is an anglo–swiss multinational commodity trading and mining company with headquarters in baar switzerland and a registered office in saint helier jersey the current company was created through a merger of glencore with xstrata on  may  as of update it ranked tenth in the fortune global  list of the worlds largest companies it is the worlds thirdlargest family business as glencore international the company was already one of the worlds leading integrated producers and marketers of commodities it was the largest company in switzerland and the worlds largest commodities trading company with a  global market share of  in internationally tradable zinc  in internationally tradable copper  percent in the internationally tradable grain market and  percent in the internationally tradable oil market glencore had a number of production facilities all around the world and supplied metals minerals crude oil oil products coal natural gas and agricultural products to international customers in the automotive power generation steel production and food processing industries the company was formed in  by a management buyout of marc rich  co ag itself founded in  it was listed on the london stock exchange in may  and was a constituent of the ftse  index it has a secondary listing on the hong kong stock exchange glencores shares started trading on the johannesburg stock exchange in november  the qatar investment authority is its biggest shareholder contents  history   formation and sale   recent finances   glencore dan gertler and the congo  associations with other mining companies   initial public offering   merger with xstrata   financial and accounting manipulations   dealings with rogue states  investments in colombia  investments in ecuador  investments in zambia  investments in the democratic republic of the congo  western sahara  ope