es opportunistic contrarian wellfunded investment approach—focusing on equity participation controlling interest and working upstream from trading relationships the acquisition was the culmination of  months of dealmaking in congo including fighting off a counterbid by former england cricketer phil edmonds starting in june  glencore and partner dan gertler an israeli mining magnate paid gb£ million for a quarterstake in mining company nikanor which was seeking to revive derelict copper mines next to katanga minings properties that deal gave glencore exclusive rights to sell all nikanors output – an offtake agreement then on christmas eve   having lost  percent of its market value over the previous six months  in the depths of the global financial crisis and  running out of cash katanga accepted a deal for about us million in a convertible loan and rights issue katanga agreed to issue more than a billion new shares and hand what would become  to glencore  by early  with copper prices regularly setting records above us a ton katangas stock market value had reached nearly us billion after a us million loss in  after acquisition it posted a  annual profit of us million in may  the company launched an ipo valuing the business at us billion and creating five new billionaires trading was limited to institutional investors for the first week and private investors werent allowed to buy shares until  may  in early  reuters reports included speculation from liberums rawlinson that after an initial public offering ipo glencore could develop an interest in londonkazakhbased eurasian natural resources corporation glencore said that contrary to recent reports it was not interested in bidding for the underfire group associations with other mining companiesedit along with several other major coal producers glencore is also a large shareholder in globalcoal the online physical coal trading platform the board of globalcoal contains a number of power utility shareholders relationships also exist with century aluminum co cenx  economic ownership interest in the us glencore partial subsidiary minara resources ltd aumre a  stake in one of australia’s top three nickel producers and  in united company rusal hk the russian aluminium giant that went public in  in mid century was called one of the most harrowing stocks of the past few years but identified as a risky but potentially profitable investment for the future  initial public offeringedit glencore was the subject of an initial public offering ipo in may  in a dual listing in london and hong kong valued at about us billion the page document revealed invaluable information about this private company that has remained discreet for thirtyseven years ivan glasenbergs shareholding was diluted from  before the ipo percent to  afterwards daniel mate and telis mistakidis zinc copper and lead codirectors were diluted from  to  glencore went public to raise gross proceeds of around  billion according to reuters glencore is known for its opportunistic but lucrative acquisition strategy in may  united arab emirates stateowned aabar investments confirmed an investment of  million in glencore international plc as a cornerstone investor with an intention to invest an additional  million in the global offer the investment made aabar the largest cornerstone investor in the initial public offering ipo and the largest new shareholder of glencore after its ipo giving aabar a  stake the two firms intend to explore areas of cooperation  in november  abu dhabis aabar investments a unit of abu dhabis stateowned united arab emirates international petroleum investment company wrote off more than million of its billion investment into glencores ipo less than two years after investing it aabar investments was the largest new shareholder in glencore  merger with xstrataedit prior to its merger with xstrata glencore is reported to have served as a marketing partner for the company as of  glencore leaders willy strothotte de and ivan glasenberg were on the board of xstrata which strothotte chaired according to the sunday times by  glencore controlled  of xstrata stock and appointed xstrata ceo mick davis in february  glencore international plc agreed to buy xstrata plc for gb£ billion us billion in shares glencore offered  new shares for each xstrata share in agreed allshare merger of equal it is the biggest mining takeover ever and after approval would create an entity with  sales of us billion in june  glencore and xstrata began to reconsider the proposed retention package for their merger following shareholder opposition to a huge payout for executives in total  key executives stood to receive over gbp  million under the initial retention package in october  bbc news reported that glencore had more ships than the british royal navy glencores operations in  countries handled  of the worlds oil consumption xstratas operations in more than  countries employed  people according to mining analyst john meyer if the two companies merged into glencore xstrata they would be the th largest commodities trader in the world just before completing its forced april  takeover of mining rival xstrata as it awaited chinese regulatory approval for its longplanned merger the worlds largest diversified commodities trader the annual income of glencore fell  percent as its trading division offset the impact of weak commodity prices including the impact of an impairment related to a reclassification of its holding in russian aluminium producer rusal net income fell  on  may  it completed the merger with xstrata on  may  glencore xstrata changed its name to glencore plc after the merger with glencore xstrata cfo trevor reid announced that he would no longer work as employee but would become a consultant after  years of involvement this marked a massive shift in the companys strategy and xstrata was entering a postreid era  financial and accounting manipulationsedit in  five nongovernment organisations filed a complaint to the oecd against a subsidiary of glencore over allegations that a mine it owns in zambia may not be paying enough tax on its profits the cause for the complaint lay in the financial and accounting manipulations performed by the two companies subsidiary mopani copper mines plc mcm to evade taxation in zambia a draft grant thornton report alleged that tax avoidance by glencore in zambia cost the zambian government hundreds of millions of dollars in lost revenue the avoidance was alleged to have been facilitated through mechanisms such as transfer pricing and inflated costs at glencores mopani copper mine the mopani mines are controlled through the british virgin islands a recognised tax haven glencore and its own auditor deloitte rejected these allegations  dealings with rogue statesedit abc radio reported in  that glencore has been accused of illegal dealings with rogue states apartheid south africa ussr iran and iraq under saddam hussein and has a history of busting un embargoes to profit from corrupt or despotic regimes specifically glencore was reported to have been named by the cia to have paid  in illegal kickbacks to obtain oil in the course of the un oilforfood programme for iraq the company denied these charges according to the cia report quoted by abc investments in colombiaedit swiss public television tsr reported in  that allegations of corruption and severe human rights violations were being raised against glencore due to the alleged conduct of its colombian cerrejón mining subsidiary local union president francisco ramirez accused cerrejón of forced expropriations and evacuations of entire villages to enable mine expansion in complicity with colombian authorities a representative of the local wayuu indians also accused colombian paramilitary and military units including those charged with cerrejón mining security of forcibly driving the wayuu off their land in what she described as a massacre a bbc investigation in  uncovered sale documents showing the company had paid the associates of paramilitary killers in colombia in  a colombian court was told by former paramilitaries that they stole the land so they could sell it to glencores subsidiary prodeco to start an opencast coal mine the court accepted their evidence and concluded that coal was the motive for the massacre glencore disputed the courts ruling glencorextratas huge coal operation in colombia prodeco was fined a total of nearly  in  for several environmental violations running in earlier years including waste disposal without a permit and producing coal without an environmental management plan glencorextratas activities in colombia under their subsidiary prodeco was investigated by the netherlandsbased ngo pax for peace they found that from  to  residents of the cesar mining region of colombia from which european power utilities source most of their coal have suffered greatly from paramilitary violence  prodeco mining companies have supported the paramilitary forces with finance equipment and information the mining companies deny any involvement but those victims of human rights violations who stand up for their rights are still being threatened the coal mined by prodeco is termed blood coal pax released a report and included the testimony of victims and the paramilitary that attacked the indigenous population investments in ecuadoredit in ecuador the current government has tried to reduce the role played by middlemen such as glencore with state oil company petroecuador due to questions about transparency and followthrough according to fernando villavicencio a quitobased oil sector analyst investments in zambiaedit according to a reuters article in  officials in zambia believe pollution from glencores mopani mine is causing acid rain and health problems in an area where  million people live the upgrade of the mopani mines asset plant was completed in march  eliminating the emissions of  per cent of sulphur dioxide emissions in line with the recommended international standards by the world health organisation who an audit report from  revealed an unexplained increase in operating costs in    million stunningly low reported volumes of extracted cobalt when compared to similar mining companies operating in the region and manipulations of copper selling prices in favor of glencore which constitute a violation of oecd’s “arm’s length” principle the result of those various processes was to lower mcm’s net income for the  period by several hundreds of millions of dollars hereby substantially lightening the company’s tax burden investments in the democratic republic of the congoedit the companys luilu copper refinery uses acid to extract the copper for three years after taking over the mine it continued to allow the waste acid to flow into a river the chief executive ivan glasenberg was interviewed for panorama by john sweeney and said it was impossible to remedy any way faster glencore said the pollution started long before the company took over the refinery and that it has now ended a reporter for the guardian found children as young as ten underground at the tilwezembe mine which the company had said in a  prospectus that it had closed due to falling copper prices these have since rebounded ceo ivan glasenberg said the company does not profit from child labor and the child miners were part of artisanal mining by nearby residents that glencore was trying to prevent but panorama tracked a shipment of copper from the mine to groupe bazano plant and from that plant to a glencore smelter in zambia they have also been accused of acquiring illicit conflict minerals in a detailed letter sent to global witness the company denied any wrongdoing glencore acquired stakes in the kansuki mine in congos southern katanga province in  according to global witness congos government transferred a  per cent stake in kansuki mine in secret and at vastly undervalued prices in july  to a company in which dan gertler who is a close friend of president joseph kabila has an interest just a month later in august  glencore took half the shares of the company that acquired that  per cent stake becoming the operator of the mine glencore is financing the entire development of the kansuki mine thereby carrying the costs for the other partner companies which are associated with mr gertler glencore said at the time during the period when these transactions took place glencore had decided in general not to increase its shareholdings in drc projects glencore acquired a  per cent share in samref congo sprl in  a congoleseregistered company holding  of the mutanda mine according to global witness samref recommended on  march  that congos staterun company gécamines holding the other  share in the mutanda mine sell this share to an entity also associated with dan gertler and went on to question the links between glencore and dan gertler glencore has been designated operator of the mutanda mine glencore has responded a number of times to global witness regarding these allegations western saharaedit in  and  a subsidiary of glencore xstrata was awarded two offshore drilling licences off the coast of occupied western sahara the licences are awarded in clear violation of international law as described by the un in  operationsedit in may  the company announced it would close its underground newlands coal mine in queensland australia in late  the mine begun in  produced  million tonnes of thermal coal in  the company had earlier suspended operations at its ravensworth underground mine following falling coal prices escalating production costs and a higher australian dollar  board of directorsedit as of october  tony hayward nonexecutive chairman ivan glasenberg ceo peter grauer nonexecutive director peter coates nonexecutive director leonhard fischer nonexecutive director william macaulay nonexecutive director john mack nonexecutive director patrice merrin nonexecutive director women on the boardedit in  glencore was listed on the london stock exchange in the same year chairman simon murray opposed quotas for women on boards claiming that women are not so ambitious in business as men because theyve got better things to do quite often they like bringing up their children and all sorts of other things remarks for which he later apologised by  glencore was the only blue chip company with no female member of the board giving it what the financial times called pariah status following criticism from government minister vince cable and objections by major shareholders including aviva investors and the local authority pension fund forum lapff glencore promised to appoint a woman director in june  glencore appointed patrice merrin as its first female director referencesedit  a b c d annual report  pdf glencore retrieved  april    glencore international on the forbes global  list forbescom  retrieved    a b glencore finishes takeover of xstrata financial times  may  retrieved  may    glencore xstrata fortune global     relatively successful daily chart the economist  november  retrieved  november  familycontrolled firms now make up  of the companies in the fortune global  which tracks the world’s largest firms by sales that is up from  in  according to new research by mckinsey a consulting firm which defines such firms as ones whose founders or their families have the biggest stake of at least  plus the power to appoint the chief executive   glencore taking over the world aljazeera – counting the cost  may  retrieved  may    a b c pidd helen glaister dan smith david cobain ian  may  the rise of glencore the biggest company youve never heard of the guardian london retrieved  may    glencores share of global commodity markets the telegraph london  april  retrieved  may    glencores shares flat on first conditional trading day bbc news  may  retrieved  may    glencore jumps into ftse  the independent  may  retrieved  may    thomas denny  may  glencores hong kong shares down  pct on trading